  "prompt": "What are some unexpected things first-time visitors to Norway notice?",
  "response": "Here are some unexpected things first-time visitors to Norway often notice:\n\n1. High Cost of Living\n- Extremely expensive food, drinks, and dining out\n- High prices for basic goods and services\n- Very costly public transportation and taxis\n\n2. Natural Beauty\n- Stunning, dramatic landscapes with fjords, mountains, and coastlines\n- Extremely long summer days and very short winter days\n- Incredible, pristine wilderness everywhere\n\n3. Cultural Differences\n- Norwegians tend to be reserved and quiet in public\n- Strong emphasis on work-life balance\n- People dress very practically and casually\n- Very punctual and organized society\n\n4. Unique Social Norms\n- Outdoor culture with lots of hiking and outdoor activities\n- Strong \"allemannsretten\" (right to roam) where people can camp and hike almost anywhere\n- High levels of trust and low crime rates\n- Less formal social interactions compared to many other countries\n\n5. Technological and Infrastructure Aspects\n- Excellent public transportation\n- Advanced electric vehicle infrastructure\n- High-speed internet everywhere\n- Modern, clean cities with efficient systems\n\n6. Food and Drink Surprises\n- Unusual traditional foods like brunost (brown cheese)\n- Strong coffee culture\n- Expensive alcohol\n- Lots of fish and seafood in the diet\n\nThese observations can vary by individual experience, but they're commonly reported by first-time visitors.",
